  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Probiotic supplementation to preterm infants have been reported to be beneficial in neonatal
      intensive care unit (NICU). Our pilot study also showed accelerated feeding in preterm
      infants who received Bifidobacterium bifidum early after birth. In order to evaluate these
      beneficial effects of Bifidobacterium bifidum, a prospective randomized control study is
      conducted. The hypothesis of the study is that Bifidobacterium bifidum supplementation to
      preterm infants improve enteral feeding and growth in very low birth weight infants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
